              "display_title": "How CNAs Break the Chain Every Day",
              "learner_facing_content": "As a CNA you break the chain every day. You attack the infectious agent through proper cleaning and disinfection. You reduce the reservoir with environmental cleaning and proper waste disposal. You close the portal of exit by covering wounds and handling linen properly. You block the mode of transmission with hand hygiene, PPE, and standard precautions. You protect the portal of entry through skin care and wound protection. And you support the susceptible host with good nutrition, mobility support, and early reporting of changes. Hand hygiene breaks the chain at the most common transmission point and is the single most effective way to prevent infection spread.",
