              "narration_script": "Dementia is not the only condition that affects cognition. You may also care for residents with: Parkinson's Disease: A progressive nervous system disorder causing tremors, stiffness, and slow movement. Dementia may develop in later stages. Cerebral Vascular Accident (CVA / Stroke): May cause paralysis, speech difficulty (aphasia), and cognitive changes depending on which area of the brain is affected. Intellectual Disability / Developmental Disability: Lifelong conditions present from birth or early childhood. Residents need individualized care plans. Mental Illness: Conditions such as bipolar disorder, schizophrenia, depression, anxiety, or PTSD. These require specific communication approaches and may require medication management by licensed staff. Epilepsy: A seizure disorder. Know each resident's seizure protocol and keep the environment safe. For all conditions: Follow the individualized care plan. Report any changes. Treat every resident with dignity and respect.",
              "transcript_text": "Dementia is not the only condition that affects cognition. You may also care for residents with: Parkinson's Disease: A progressive nervous system disorder causing tremors, stiffness, and slow movement. Dementia may develop in later stages. Cerebral Vascular Accident (CVA / Stroke): May cause paralysis, speech difficulty (aphasia), and cognitive changes depending on which area of the brain is affected. Intellectual Disability / Developmental Disability: Lifelong conditions present from birth or early childhood. Residents need individualized care plans. Mental Illness: Conditions such as bipolar disorder, schizophrenia, depression, anxiety, or PTSD. These require specific communication approaches and may require medication management by licensed staff. Epilepsy: A seizure disorder. Know each resident's seizure protocol and keep the environment safe. For all conditions: Follow the individualized care plan. Report any changes. Treat every resident with dignity and respect.",
