              "display_title": "Readiness for Mobility Assistance",
              "learner_facing_content": "Before mobility assistance, CCCCO Module 14 says to consider whether the resident can be more independent by checking physical strength and ability, available special training, assistive devices, financial resources, cognitive ability, and motivation. In CNA practice, you do not perform a formal therapy assessment, but you do observe readiness and follow the care plan.\n\nAsk: Can the resident follow directions today? Is the assigned device present? Is the resident weaker, dizzy, short of breath, in pain, or more confused than usual? Can the resident sit steadily or stand briefly as directed? If readiness changes, report before proceeding.",
