              "display_title": "Transfer Safety and Help Requirements",
              "learner_facing_content": "The CCCCO source directs staff to follow facility policy on lifting and transferring. It also identifies situations needing extra caution, including residents over 100 pounds, osteoporosis, and transfers requiring team lift or mechanical assistance. The safest rule is to use the care plan and facility policy, not guesswork.\n\nIf the resident cannot assist as expected, if equipment is missing, if the lift plan is unclear, or if you feel unsafe, stop and get help. Do not drag, twist, rush, or perform a transfer alone when the plan calls for help. A delayed transfer is safer than an unsafe transfer.",
