              "display_title": "Osteoporosis and Fracture Precautions",
              "learner_facing_content": "CCCCO Module 13 describes osteoporosis as lost bone mass that leaves bones porous, spongy, and easily fractured. It notes that fractures can occur from little or no trauma, and that fractured hip is often related to falling and osteoporosis. CNA care emphasizes preventing further fractures, reporting pain, gentle handling, ordered splints or braces, mechanical lift when required, and gentle positioning.\n\nIf a resident falls, has severe hip or knee pain, cannot get up, has a shortened or externally rotated leg, or has swelling/bruising after movement, do not move the resident unless directed for immediate safety. Call for the nurse and follow facility emergency policy.",
