              "display_title": "Common Nutrients and Food Sources",
              "learner_facing_content": "CCCCO Module 11 lists common nutrients with food sources and functions. Carbohydrates from grains, pastas, breads, cereals, fruits, and vegetables are a main energy source and provide fiber. Proteins from eggs, milk, meat, fish, nuts, poultry, cheese, beans, peanut butter, and soy products support tissue growth and repair. Fats from oils, milk, cream, cheese, meats, butter, and mayonnaise provide energy, help carry vitamins, conserve body heat, and protect internal organs.\n\nVitamins and minerals are found in many foods and help regulate body functions and repair tissue. Dietary fiber from raw fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and cereals adds bulk for normal bowel elimination.",
