              "display_title": "Fluids, Minimum Intake, and Water Functions",
              "learner_facing_content": "CCCCO Module 11 notes that a balanced diet includes enough fluids and gives approximately 1500 milliliters per day as a minimum adult fluid reference unless the care plan restricts fluids. The source also identifies water, juices, and other beverages as fluid sources and states that water is essential for normal body function because chemical reactions in the body take place in water.\n\nFor CNA practice, this supports careful observation. If a resident has force fluids, fluid restriction, thickened liquids, or I&O orders, follow the care plan exactly. Encourage allowed fluids, keep water or ordered beverages in reach when appropriate, document intake accurately, and report poor intake, dark urine, dizziness, confusion, dry mouth, or sudden output changes.",
