              "display_title": "Tube Feeding: CNA Observation Boundaries",
              "learner_facing_content": "CCCCO Module 11 states that tube feedings are ordered by the doctor and started by a licensed nurse. The CNA does not start, stop, adjust, or troubleshoot the feeding pump independently.\n\nThe CNA observation role is still important. Monitor for pressure on or kinking of tubing, watch the feeding level and report when it is low, keep the head of bed elevated as ordered by the care plan, and notify the licensed nurse of pump alarms or signs and symptoms of aspiration. If repositioning is needed, protect the tubing and follow the care plan. The safety rule is observe, protect, report, and do not adjust the order or equipment.",
