              "display_title": "Pressure Injury Prevention Bundle",
              "learner_facing_content": "The CCCCO source lists prevention measures that are directly relevant to CNA work: change position at least every two hours or as ordered, remind or help seated residents shift weight, support proper nutrition and hydration, remove feces or urine promptly, inspect skin whenever personal care is given, remove wrinkles and foreign objects from linens, avoid hot water and friction, and separate body areas to prevent rubbing.\n\nPrevention is easier than treatment. Use turning sheets or other assigned aids for dependent residents, avoid dragging, keep heels protected as ordered, and report signs immediately to the licensed nurse. Do not improvise devices or treatments that are not in the care plan.",
