              "display_title": "Devices, Tubing, Braces, and Bed Position",
              "learner_facing_content": "CCCCO Module 13 includes mechanical aids and pressure checks in prevention: alternating-pressure mattresses, pillows for bridging, gel or air cushions, heel protectors, and turning sheets may be used according to the care plan. It also tells staff to check improperly fitted braces or restraints and check tubing for rubbing.\n\nThe CNA does not select or order the device independently. The CNA checks that assigned equipment is in place, notices slipping, bunching, rubbing, tubing pressure, damp linens, wrinkles, or a head-of-bed position that conflicts with the care plan, and reports concerns. If an ordered device is missing or causing pressure, escalate to the nurse.",
