        "recommended_response": "Position the resident seated or lying with the arm supported at heart level. Select the correct cuff size. Apply the cuff smoothly 2-3 cm above the antecubital fossa. Inflate to 180 mmHg or 30 mmHg above the last known systolic. Deflate at 2-3 mmHg per second. Record the first Korotkoff sound as systolic and the disappearance of sound as diastolic. Document the reading, date, time, arm used, and position. Report any reading significantly outside his baseline to the licensed nurse immediately.",
        "refresh_resource": "Module 5 Lesson 5.4; Skills Refresh Menu Topic 8",
        "status": "Optional - not graded - not certificate-gated",
        "source_reference": "CNA-Recert-Course/Content/clinical-support/confidence-checks/33_OPTIONAL_CLINICAL_CONFIDENCE_CHECKS_COMPLETE.md",
        "sme_review_flag": "None identified",
        "compliance_review_flag": "Do not store as CE evidence; do not label as competency validation."
